The Carnavalet museum is the one you must visit if you want to learn more about the history of Paris from prehistory to today. And then if we are only moderately interested, we can always just enjoy the two private mansions located in the heart of the Marais district which house the museum! Unfortunately the museum has been closed for 3 years since October 2016 üöß.

it was good, there were superb portraits but the museum was not very big. The garden is superb and if you are interested in the French revolution this is the right museum! Lots of very realistic portraits: I love them. the garden is perfect for a picnic or a coffee
